'''Uğurcan Çakır''' (born 5 April 1996) is a Turkish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Trabzonspor ===
Çakır made his senior debut for [[Trabzonspor]] in a 1–0 loss to [[Rabotnicki Skopje]] during the qualifying rounds of the [[UEFA Europa League]]. He later played three matches in the [[Turkish Cup]], keeping two clean sheets. After these appearances, he established himself as the club's second-choice goalkeeper, remaining on the bench until January without making any appearances in the [[Super Lig]].

Like many young Trabzonspor goalkeepers, Çakır was loaned to the club's local affiliate [[1461 Trabzon]] on 15 January 2016. He made his senior debut for the club in a 2–1 win over [[Yeni Malatyaspor]]. He continued as 1461 Trabzon's first-choice goalkeeper for three additional appearances in the [[TFF First League]], conceding seven goals without keeping a clean sheet. He later suffered an ankle injury that kept him out for two months. After returning, he played four more matches but was eventually dropped due to underwhelming performances. His one-year loan spell was cut short, and he returned to Trabzonspor on 30 June 2016.

Following his return, Çakır did not make any appearances for Trabzonspor in any competition, largely due to his performances during the previous loan spell with 1461 Trabzon. He was named on the bench for two Super Lig matches and most Turkish Cup fixtures.

Çakır eventually made his Trabzonspor debut at the age of 21 on 22 September 2017 against [[Alanyaspor]]. He came on at halftime after first-choice goalkeeper [[Esteban Alvarado]] was forced off with an injury. Trabzonspor had been leading 3–1 at halftime but ultimately lost the match 4–3 after two penalties were awarded to the opposition. Despite the defeat, Çakır impressed manager [[Ersun Yanal]], which led to him starting the final five matches of the [[Super Lig]] season. During that period he conceded twelve goals and kept one clean sheet, continuing his development as a young goalkeeper.

Çakır later reaffirmed his role as the second-choice goalkeeper for Trabzonspor. However, after first-choice goalkeeper [[Onur Kivrak]] retired on 16 January 2019, he became the club's primary goalkeeper. He went on to play eighteen matches in the Super Lig, conceding twenty goals and recording two clean sheets.

He won his first trophy with the club by lifting the [[2019–20 Turkish Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/trabzonspor-win-turkish-cup-156993 |title=Trabzonspor win Ziraat Turkish Cup |publisher=Hürriyet Daily News |date=30 July 2020 }}</ref> He was named as club's captain ahead of the 2020–21 season following the departure of [[José Sosa]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200830163612/https://www.fotomac.com.tr/trabzonspor/2020/08/29/sosadan-sonra-trabzonsporun-yeni-kaptani-ugurcan-cakir-oldu |title=Sosa'dan sonra Trabzonspor'un yeni kaptanı Uğurcan Çakır oldu |publisher=fotomac.com |language=tr |date=29 August 2020 }}</ref> He later achieved the [[2021–22 Süper Lig]] title, which marked Trabzonspor's first league championship in 38 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/trabzonspor-wins-turkish-super-lig-title-after-38-year-hiatus |title=Trabzonspor wins Turkish Süper Lig title after 38-year hiatus |publisher=Daily Sabah |date=30 April 2022 }}</ref>

=== Galatasaray ===
On 2 September 2025, [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] announced that they reached an agreement with Trabzonspor for the transfer of Çakır for €27.5&nbsp;million transfer fee. Çakır, who signed a five-year contract with Galatasaray, will receive €2.5&nbsp;million of guaranteed money and bonuses annually.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/ugurcan-cakir-galatasarayda/58393|title=Uğurcan Çakır Galatasaray'da!|publisher=[[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]]|date=2 September 2025|access-date=2 September 2025|language=tr}}</ref> On 13 September, he made his debut with the team against [[Eyüpspor]] with a [[clean sheet]] in a 2–0 away [[Süper Lig]] win.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/ikas-eyupspor-0-2-galatasaray/58447|title=İkas Eyüpspor 0-2 Galatasaray|publisher=[[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]]|date=13 September 2025|access-date=19 September 2025|language=tr}}</ref> On 18 September, he made his continental debut with the team against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in a 5–1 [[UEFA Champions League]] away defeat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/sampiyonlar-ligi/eintracht-frankfurt-5-1-galatasaray/58475|title=Eintracht Frankfurt 5-1 Galatasaray|publisher=[[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]]|date=19 September 2025|access-date=19 September 2025|language=tr}}</ref>

==International career==
Çakır made his debut for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] on 30 May 2019, in a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] against [[Greece national football team|Greece]], as a starter.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=540122|title=Turkey v Greece game report|date=30 May 2019}}</ref>

In June 2021, he was included in the list of 26 Turkish players to compete for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=35271 |title=A Millî Takımın nihai kadrosu açıklandı |trans-title=Final squad of the national team announced |work=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=1 June 2021 |access-date=1 June 2021 |language=tr}}</ref> On 7 June 2024, he was named in the final list of 26 players selected by [[Vincenzo Montella]] to compete for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın Euro 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=Euro 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref>

